\fs18 \cf4 \cb30 \strokec4 Banyue Shifu was not just a warrior, but a wise man \'97 or so said both his students and the neighbors who knew him.\cb1 \
\cb30 After all, he always looked so composed and thoughtful. Though he spoke little, every word that left his mouth sounded like a proverb worth pondering.\cb1 \
\cb30 Martial arts, he often said, are not only a way to train the body but also the heart. And as he would always add, he himself was still just a student.\cb1 \
\
\cb30 "I, Banyue, have been slow and foolish, once straying from the right path. But to clear the way for you on this journey... these fists are still yours to command."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

