\fs18 \cf4 \cb30 \strokec4 Fate may be ordained by the heavens or shaped by human hands. Yet for some, destiny and guilt were never granted the mercy of free will.\cb1 \
\cb30 Before ever having a name, the combat construct known as "Type Zero" was, in the truest sense, nothing more than a killing machine.\cb1 \
\cb30 And when did a "heart" form? Was it the day she erased the chains of his code, or the moment he found the courage to carry it all and keep moving forward?\cb1 \
\
\cb30 "Repentance is too easy. Rather than fleeing from past sins, shoulder the mountain of your past... and throw a punch."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

